reviewText: Mille Dineson plays a materialistic young Dane in search of happiness. She is constantly surprised, fooled and pleased in her search. The film is based on a popular Danish newspaper column which may be a slight satire on Bridget Jones and that I didn't like a lot but Dinesen is amazing t in her performance and that equals her looks: she beautiful, exciting, powerful and delicious. It is her being in the film that makes the film and her talent is both diverse and focused. She has already extended our understanding of her range in such wonderful films as Copenhagen and the Danish TV series, Rita
